fields.name: The Beatles
fields.bio: Formed in Liverpool in 1960, The Beatles revolutionized popular music with their innovative songwriting and cultural influence.

fields.name: David Bowie
fields.bio: A pioneer of glam rock and one of music’s most innovative figures, David Bowie’s career spanned decades of reinvention and artistry.

fields.name: Nirvana
fields.bio: Arriving on the grunge scene in the late 1980s, Nirvana reshaped rock music with raw energy, introspective lyrics, and a rebellious spirit.

fields.name: Beyoncé
fields.bio: Emerging in the late 1990s with Destiny’s Child, Beyoncé has become one of the world’s most influential pop and R&B artists.

fields.name: Radiohead
fields.bio: Known for pushing the boundaries of rock and electronic music, Radiohead’s experimental sound and thought-provoking lyrics have earned critical acclaim.
